//! Numeric behaviors and types.
//!
//! This module provides behaviors for numeric operations that go beyond
//! the basic arithmetic operators, as well as wrapper types for different
//! overflow handling strategies.
//!
//! # Core Behaviors
//!
//! | Behavior | Description |
//! |----------|-------------|
//! | [`Zero`] | Types with an additive identity (zero) |
//! | [`One`] | Types with a multiplicative identity (one) |
//! | [`Bounded`] | Types with minimum and maximum values |
//! | [`Integer`] | Marker for integer types |
//!
//! # Overflow-Handling Wrappers
//!
//! | Type | Description |
//! |------|-------------|
//! | [`Saturating`] | Arithmetic that saturates at bounds |
//! | [`Wrapping`] | Arithmetic that wraps around on overflow |
//! | [`NonZero`] | Wrapper guaranteeing a non-zero value |
//!
//! # Overflow-Handling Behaviors
//!
//! | Behavior | Description |
//! |----------|-------------|
//! | [`CheckedAdd`], etc. | Checked arithmetic returning Maybe |
//! | [`SaturatingAdd`], etc. | Saturating arithmetic |
//! | [`WrappingAdd`], etc. | Wrapping arithmetic |
//! | [`OverflowingAdd`], etc. | Returns (result, overflowed) |
//!
//! # Examples
//!
//! ## Using Zero and One
//!
//! ```tml
//! use core::num::{Zero, One}
//!
//! func sum_or_zero[T: Zero + Add](values: List[T]) -> T {
//!     let mut result: T = T::zero()
//!     for v in values {
//!         result = result + v
//!     }
//!     return result
//! }
//! ```
//!
//! ## Using Saturating Arithmetic
//!
//! ```tml
//! use core::num::Saturating
//!
//! let x: Saturating[I8] = Saturating::new(100)
//! let y: Saturating[I8] = Saturating::new(50)
//! let sum = x + y  // Saturates to 127 instead of overflowing
//! ```

